SUMMARY:An Odd Night in the Forest
DESCRIPTION:The Davis Odd Fellows will host\, “An Odd Night in the Forest” on Sunday\, March 15th\, from 7-9 pm at the Davis Odd Fellows Hall\, 415 2nd St. We will show the film\, “The Man Who Planted Trees\,” and there will be a presentation by Tree Davis about our City’s trees and what the community can do to help plant trees. The even is free and open to the entire community. Doors will open at 6:30. Refreshments will be for sale.
